parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The steering wheel shake or vibration can cause the vehicle to pull to one side, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes or vibrates between 60-80 mph
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel oscillates
the cabin vibrates
and the vehicle does not track well in its lane.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering rack can cause the vehicle to lose steering control, making it difficult or impossible to control, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The steering wheel shudders or vibrates
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel binds or locks up while turning
and the steering rack needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Air Bag Control Module and Assembly Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the air bag control module and assembly can cause the air bags to malfunction, which can lead to accidents or injuries in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The horn fails to work
the steering wheel malfunctions
and the air bag control module and assembly are corroded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected explosion of the sunroof glass can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries due to the shock and distraction of the event.
symptoms: The sunroof glass shatters or explodes without any apparent reason
sending glass and debris into the vehicle
and potentially causing the driver to swerve or lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water accumulation in the spare tire well can lead to water damage, corrosion, and electrical issues, potentially causing safety hazards and costly repairs.
symptoms: Water accumulates in the spare tire well
especially during rain
and may cause water damage
corrosion
or electrical issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unpredictable jerking motion of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences an intermittent jerking motion
often accompanied by a loss of power
which can cause the vehicle to slow down or speed up unexpectedly
leading to a loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: AC Evaporation Valve Blockage and Water Accumulation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The blockage of the AC evaporation valve can cause water accumulation in the footwells, leading to water damage, corrosion, and safety hazards due to slippery pedals.
symptoms: Water accumulates in the driver and passenger footwells
causing water damage
corrosion
and slippery pedals
which can lead to accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high pressure fuel pump can cause the engine to shut off, leading to a loss of power, power steering, and brakes, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off
loss of power
loss of power steering
loss of brakes
sudden failure of the fuel pump
disintegration of the fuel pump sending aluminum "shrapnel" through the fuel system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Add Blue heater system can cause the vehicle to emit excessive pollutants, which can lead to environmental harm and potential health risks.
symptoms: The Add Blue heater system fails
the vehicle emits excessive pollutants
the system fails prematurely (less than 42
000 miles).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and throttle issues can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the vehicle loses power
the throttle malfunctions
the steering wheel shakes at high speeds (65-70 mph).
